HEADWORD: Editor
<hw>Ed"i*tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., that which
produces, from <ets>edere</ets> to publish: cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧diteur</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who edits; esp., a person who
prepares, superintends, revises, and corrects a book, magazine, or
newspaper, etc., for publication.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

